 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Senior Information Specialist The Queen's Medical Center 68 reviews Hawaii Full-time The Queen's Medical Center 68 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Responsibilities 
 
 
 I. JOB SUMMARY/RESPONSIBILITIES: 
Leads the planning and development of multiple, diverse, information systems and services. Consults, analyzes, plans, designs, recommends, reviews, programs, tests and monitors services related to the development, implementation, utilization and financial impact of end user products, utilities, services, application and operating systems. Participates in information system planning with assigned areas, both short and long term: reviews technical advancements applying cost and technical considerations; business consultant in setting priorities and recommending technical directions based on programs, systems, services, resources and available technology. 
 
II. TYPICAL PHYSICAL DEMANDS: 
Continuous: seeing, speaking; repetitive arm/hand motions. Frequent: standing, sitting, walking, finger dexterity, hearing. Occasional: stooping/bending; lifting and carrying usual amount of 12 pounds; reaching above shoulder level. Operates computer equipment and copying machines. 
 
III. TYPICAL WORKING CONDITIONS: 
Not substantially subjected to adverse environmental conditions. 
 
IV. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS: 
A. Education/Certification and Licensure: 
1. Bachelor's degree in Information sciences/Computer Science or related field or equivalent in work experience. 
2. Knowledge of computer technology as related to telecommunications, mainframes, microcomputers, networks, required. 
3. Training or experience in advanced analysis and design techniques. 
4. Comprehensive understanding in multiple areas of hospital systems, including business information systems and technological aspects that affect the hospital. 
 
B. Experience: 
1. Ten (10) years experience in information systems, specifically in three (3) or more of the following areas: applications design, selection, implementation and support, on line transaction processing systems, systems integration, systems software, performance evaluation and tuning, automated systems and operations, artificial intelligence, expert systems, and design, implementation, tuning and support. 
2. Three (3) years experience in systems integration. 
3. Three (3) years experience in hospital financial and clinical applications. 
4. Five (5) years experience in project management. 
